        <h3>Your Own Site</h3>
        To create your own version of this site, clone the github project
        to gain complete control.
        
        As an instructor, typically you would require your IT department to set up the
        website, and to assist in installation of the development tools on your computer.
        However, once that is done, you can maintain the site, updating content whenever you
        wish by yourself. This only requires basic computer literacy.
        
        <h3>Site Preview</h3>
        There is a very powerful facility that allows you to editor content, 
        then immediately review the site on your own browser locally. 
        Once everything is debugged, the new content is uploaded to the public site.
        
